tory. Amply illustrated with more than seventy images from diverse religious traditions, this masterful interdisciplinary study provides a comprehensive and accessible resource for everyone interested in how religious images and visual practice order space and time, communicate with the transcendent, and embody forms of communion with the divine. The Sacred Gaze is a vital introduction to the study of the visual culture of religions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aArt and religion. 0aArt et religion. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh  aafrica.  aamerica.  achristianity.  acomparative religion.  acontemporary.  across cultural.  adivine communion.  agender and masculinity.  ahistorical review.  aintellectual experiences.  ajapan.  anonfiction.  aperception.  apractical analysis.  areligious imagery.  areligious scholars.  areligious studies.  areligious traditions.  areligious visual culture.  asacred gaze.  asense making.  asocial experience.  aspiritual significance.  athailand.  atheoretical perspective.  atibet.  atranscendence.  avisual culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024306440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093830440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938304423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938304/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles